orth Shore had won the championship the league decided to play a knockout competition between the four remaining teams. Newton and City both won their matches and progressed to the final.\n\n======Round 1======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 21 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = 17\u20130\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =The \"Knockout\" Competition/Champions Beaten by Newton/City Defeat Ponsonby\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15335\n| date = 1913-06-23\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130623.2.134.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>\n| away =North Shore\n| try1 = Clarke 3, A Healey, [[Graham Cook]]\n| con1 = Jim Bennett\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium =Auckland Domain\n| attendance = 2000\n| referee = J Fielding\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 21 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 14\u20137\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =The \"Knockout\" Competition/Champions Beaten by Newton/City Defeat Ponsonby\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15335\n| date = 1913-06-23\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130623.2.134.2\n| accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = Dunkley, Watene\n| con1 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| pen1 = [[Albert Asher]] 3\n| try2 = McCallum\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]], Cross\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 3500\n| referee = Murray\n}}\n\n======Knockout Final======\nCity were joined by [[Jim Rukutai]] for the match following Manukau\u2019s senior team disbanding.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 5 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 25\u20135\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =The Knock-out Final/City Rovers Team on Top/Newton Beaten by 25 to 5\n| page =7\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLIV| issue=160\n| date = 1913-07-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19130707.2.68.3\n| accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = Harold Denize, [[Don Kenealy]] 2, Robinson, Watene\n| con1 = [[Albert Asher]] 4\n| pen1 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| try2 = Bowen\n| con2 = [[Graham Cook]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = Knox\n}}\n\n===Top Scorers===\nA large number of matches did not have the scorers named meaning the following lists are incomplete. Points missing are as follows: Newton Rangers (22), City Rovers (18), Ponsonby United (25), Eden Ramblers (15), and Manukau Rovers (18). The scorers for the knockout matches are also included.\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Player!!Team!!Tries\n|-\n|1||C Clark||Newton Rangers||10\n|-\n|2||George Cook||Newton Rangers||7\n|-\n|3||Watene||City Rovers||4\n|-\n|3||[[Stan Weston]]||North Shore Albions||4\n|-\n|5||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||North Shore Albions||3\n|-\n|5||Ike Healey||Newton Rangers||3\n|-\n|5||[[Harry Fricker]]||Ponsonby United||3\n|-\n|}\n \n{{col-2}}\n \n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!No!!Name!!Tries!!Con!!Pen!!Marks!!Drops!!Points\n|-\n|1||[[Albert Asher]]||2||9||9||-||-||42\n|-\n|2||[[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]]||2||8||3||4||1||38\n|-\n|3||George Cook||7||4||2||-||-||33\n|-\n|4||C Clark||10||1||-||-||-||32\n|-\n|5||[[Karl Ifwersen]]||3||1||2||-||-||15\n|-\n|6||Jim Bennett||2||3||1||-||-||14\n|-\n|7||[[George Seagar]]||-||4||2||-||-||12\n|-\n|7||[[Stan Weston]]||4||-||-||-||-||12\n|-\n|}\n\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Thacker Shield==\nOn 7 September North Shore Albions journeyed to Christchurch to play against Sydenham to play for the Thacker Shield. At the start of the season Dr. Thacker, president of the Canterbury league had presented the shield for competition amongst the senior clubs of Christchurch but he had stipulated that it was open to competition to any club in New Zealand. When North Shore won the Auckland championship they immediately issued a challenge to Sydenham. North Shore sent a strong team south but were without [[Karl Ifwersen]] and [[Stan Walters]] who were representing New Zealand against the touring New South Wales side.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 September\n| time =3:00\n| home =Sydenham\n| score =13\u20138\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n| title =Thacker Shield Match\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15400\n| date = 1913-09-08\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130908.2.8.1\n| accessdate = 2019-12-27}}</ref>\n| away =North Shore Albions\n| try1 =Kirton, Smythe 2\n| con1 =Smith 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =Pullen, Rogers\n| con2 =[[George Seagar]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium =Christchurch Showgrounds\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n==Representative Season==\n1913 was a busy year for the [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] representative team as they played 8 matches for a 7 win, 1 loss record. Their only defeat was against the touring [[New South Wales rugby league team|New South Wales]] team.\n\nThe first representative fixture of the season was played on 28 June against a Country selection at [[Victoria Park, Auckland]]. Three thousand spectators attended and 117 pounds was collected. Further matches were played against [[Taranaki rugby league team|Taranaki]], [[Hawke's Bay rugby league team|Hawke's Bay]], Nelson, [[Canterbury rugby league team|Canterbury]], [[Wellington rugby league team|Wellington]], and [[New South Wales rugby league team|New South Wales]]. [[Auckland rugby league team|Auckland]] also played an exhibition match in [[Pukekohe]] against the Auckland club champions North Shore Albions.\n\n===Representative Matches===\n======Auckland v Country Combined======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 28 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 10\u20138\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n  | title =Auckland Defeat Country/Dufty\u2019s Fine Kicking\n  | page =4\n  | work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15341\n  | date = 1913-06-30\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130630.2.7.1\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>\n| away = Country Combined\n| try1 = George Cook, [[Jim Griffen|Jim Griffin]]\n| con1 = [[George Seagar]]\n| pen1 = [[George Seagar]]\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Dufty 4\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = Harker\n}}\n\n======Auckland v Taranaki (Northern Union Cup)======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 1 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 24\u20138\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n  | title = The First Challenge Match/Auckland Retain the Cup/Taranaki Easily Defeated\n  | page =4\n  | work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15352\n  | date = 1913-07-14\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130714.2.8.1\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Taranaki\n| try1 = George Cook], [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]] 2, [[Arthur Carlaw]], [[Karl Ifwersen]] 2\n| con1 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]] 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Taylor 2\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = Hooker (mark)\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 5000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n======Auckland V Hawke\u2019s Bay (Northern Union Cup)======\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 26 July\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Auckland\n| score = 34\u20137\n| report =<ref>{{cite news\n  | title =Auckland Defeats Hawke's Bay/By 34 Points to 7/A Spectacular Game\n  | page =4\n  | work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15364\n  | date = 1913-07-28\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130728.2.9.1\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>| away = Hawke\u2019s Bay\n| try1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 4, [[Albert Asher]], [[Harold Hayward]], [[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]], [[Bob Mitchell (rugby league)|Bob Mitchell]]\n| con1 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]], [[Karl Ifwersen]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = [[Jim Johnson (rugby league)|Jim Johnson]]\n| con2 = A Morrison\n| pen2 = A Morrison (mark)\n| stadium