serve\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n======Round 4======\nIn the Ponsonby match with North Shore [[Harry Fricker]] was ordered off for striking an opponent. The act was missed by the referee but seen by the line umpire. The match between Manukau and Eden was reported as a win to Manukau and a win to Eden in differing reports.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 5\u20130\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =City Defeat Newton\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15311\n| date = 1913-05-26\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130526.2.132.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| con1 =\n| pen1 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 2500\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 17\u20137\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Wins for Shore and Manukau\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15311\n| date = 1913-05-26\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130526.2.132.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = [[Stan Weston]] 2, [[Karl Ifwersen]] 2, [[Stan Walters (rugby league)|Stan Walters]]\n| con1 = E Rogers\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = unknown x 1\n| con2 = unknown x 1\n| pen2 = [[Charles Savory]]\n| stadium = Devonport Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee = Benson\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 24 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Manukau\n| score = 10\u201311\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title = Wins for Shore and Manukau\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15311\n| date = 1913-05-26\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130526.2.132.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Eden\n| try1 = unknown x 2\n| con1 = unknown x 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = unknown x 3\n| con2 = unknown x 1\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Onehunga Recreation Reserve\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n======Round 5======\nManukau defaulted their match to North Shore Albions. The later arrived in Onehunga to find that their opponents could not muster a team. [[Jim Rukutai]] and other prominent players were said to be suffering from influenza.<ref>{{cite news\n| title =NS Albions v Manukau Rovers\n| page = 8\n| work=[[Auckland Star]]| volume=XLIV| issue=130\n| date = 1913-06-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/AS19130602.2.110.1\n| accessdate = 2019-12-09}}</ref> This was to be [[Manukau Magpies|Manukau\u2019s]] last game in the senior grade for decades as they forfeited the following week along with Eden and dropped out of the senior competition. Eden were to cease playing as a club a few seasons later and never returned.\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 8\u20135\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n  | title =First Round Concluded/North Shore in the Lead\n  | page =9\n  | work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15317\n  | date = 1913-06-02\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130602.2.124\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Newton\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =[[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]]\n| drop1 =[[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]] 3\n| try2 = George Cook\n| con2 = Len Farrant\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 3000\n| referee = E R Harker\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = City\n| score = 18\u20132\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =First Round Concluded/North Shore in the Lead\n| page =9\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15317\n| date = 1913-06-02\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130602.2.124\n| accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = Eden\n| try1 = unknown x 4\n| con1 = unknown x 3\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 = unknown x 1\n| stadium = Auckland Domain\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 31 May\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Manukau\n| score = LBD-WBD\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n  | title =First Round Concluded/North Shore in the Lead\n  | page =9\n  | work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15317\n  | date = 1913-06-02\n  | url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130602.2.124\n  | accessdate = 2019-08-10}}</ref>| away = North Shore\n| try1 =\n| con1 =\n| pen1 =\n| try2 =\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Onehunga Recreation Reserve\n| attendance =\n| referee =\n}}\n\n======Round 6======\nA somewhat unusual event occurred in the match between Ponsonby and North Shore when it was briefly suspended after a player from North Shore dropped his false teeth. He was inevitably subjected to some \u201cgood-natured banter from the crowd\u201d.\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Ponsonby\n| score = 22\u201312\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Two Leading Teams Beaten/Wins for Ponsonby and Newton\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15323\n| date = 1913-06-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19130609.2.6.1\n| accessdate = 2019-08-12}}</ref>| away = North Shore\n| try1 = Hayward, [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]]\n| con1 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]] 2\n| pen1 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]]\n| drop1 = [[Charles Webb (rugby league)|Charles Webb]] 2\n| try2 = Ernie Bailey, E Rogers\n| con2 = [[George Seagar]] 2\n| pen2 = [[George Seagar]]\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 4000\n| referee = Knox\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 7 June\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Newton\n| score = 17\u201312\n| report = <ref>{{cite news\n| title =Two Leading Teams Beaten/Wins for Ponsonby and Newton\n| page =4\n| work=[[The New Zealand Herald]]| volume=L| issue=15323\n| date = 1913-06-07\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZ