{"title_page": "Aaron Taylor (footballer)", "text_new": "{{about|the English soccer player|the American footballers|Aaron Taylor (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Aaron Taylor\n| image    = \n| fullname = Aaron Mark Taylor\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1990|3|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Morecambe]], England\n| height =\n| currentclub = [[Witton Albion F.C.|Witton Albion]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| years1 = 2008\u20132010\n| years2 = 2009\n| years3 = 2010\n| years4 = 2010\n| years5 = 2010\n| clubs1 = [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]]\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Barrow A.F.C.|Barrow]] (loan)\n| clubs3 = [[Kendal Town F.C.|Kendal Town]]\n| clubs4 = [[Witton Albion F.C.|Witton Albion]]\n| clubs5 = [[Bamber Bridge F.C.|Bamber Bridge]]\n| caps1 = 20 \n| goals1 = 2\n| caps2 = 5\n| goals2 = 0\n| caps3 = \n| goals3 = \n| caps4 = \n| goals4 = \n| club-update = 15:48, 25 May 2010 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Aaron Mark Taylor''' is an English professional [[football striker]]. He currently plays for [[Bamber Bridge F.C.]] having previously been at [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]].\n\nTaylor was signed from the academy and made his debut as a sub in [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]]'s 2\u20132 draw with [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]]. He made his full debut against [[Rochdale F.C.|Rochdale]] on 18 October 2008 and marked his full debut with a goal.<ref>\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_3/7665162.stm Morecambe 1-1 Rochdale]\", [[BBC Sport]] (18 October 2008).</ref> He regularly featured in [[Sammy McIlroy]]s side.\n\nHe then went on to start the FA Cup game against Grimsby in the 1st round. He scored twice and was named man of the match to continue fulfilling his shown potential.<ref>\"[http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-180566852.html Aaron follows his dad into Morecambe team.]{{dead link|date=February 2019|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}\", ''The Visitor'' (Morecambe) via HighBeam (24 June 2008).</ref> He joined Barrow on a five-week loan at the start of the 2009/10 season before returning to Morecambe. He was released by Morecambe in May 2010.<ref>\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/morecambe/8703242.stm Morecambe release forward Wayne Curtis]\", ''BBC Sport'' (UK) (25 May 2010).</ref>\n\nHe signed for [[Kendal Town F.C.|Kendal Town]], before switching to [[Witton Albion F.C.|Witton Albion]] on 22 October 2010.<ref>http://www.northwichguardian.co.uk/sport/8472033.Taylor_arrival_boosts_Albion___s_attack/</ref>\n\nHe quickly moved back to Lancashire to join [[Bamber Bridge F.C.|Bamber Bridge]] on 26 November 2010.\nAaron has also played for England youth.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080927102903/http://www.morecambefc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0%2C%2C10866~43789%2C00.html Aaron Taylor profile] at Morecambe F.C.\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Taylor, Aaron (Footballer)}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Morecambe F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Barrow A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Kendal Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Witton Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bamber Bridge F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-1990s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{about|the English soccer player|the American footballers|Aaron Taylor (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=June 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Aaron Taylor\n| image    = \n| fullname = Aaron Mark Taylor\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1990|3|9}}\n| birth_place = [[Morecambe]], England\n| height = {{height|m=1.73}}\n| currentclub = [[Witton Albion F.C.|Witton Albion]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| years1 = 2008\u20132010\n| years2 = 2009\n| years3 = 2010\n| years4 = 2010\n| years5 = 2010\n| clubs1 = [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]]\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Barrow A.F.C.|Barrow]] (loan)\n| clubs3 = [[Kendal Town F.C.|Kendal Town]]\n| clubs4 = [[Witton Albion F.C.|Witton Albion]]\n| clubs5 = [[Bamber Bridge F.C.|Bamber Bridge]]\n| caps1 = 20 \n| goals1 = 2\n| caps2 = 5\n| goals2 = 0\n| caps3 = \n| goals3 = \n| caps4 = \n| goals4 = \n| club-update = 15:48, 25 May 2010 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Aaron Mark Taylor''' is an English professional [[football striker]]. He currently plays for [[Bamber Bridge F.C.]] having previously been at [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]].\n\nTaylor was signed from the academy and made his debut as a sub in [[Morecambe F.C.|Morecambe]]'s 2-2 draw with [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]]. He made his full debut against [[Rochdale F.C.|Rochdale]] on 18 October 2008 and marked his full debut with a goal.<ref>\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/eng_div_3/7665162.stm Morecambe 1-1 Rochdale]\", [[BBC Sport]] (18 October 2008).</ref> He regularly featured in [[Sammy McIlroy]]s side.\n\nHe then went on to start the FA Cup game against Grimsby in the 1st round. He scored twice and was named man of the match to continue fulfilling his shown potential.<ref>\"[http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-180566852.html Aaron follows his dad into Morecambe team.]{{dead link|date=February 2019|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}\", ''The Visitor'' (Morecambe) via HighBeam (24 June 2008).</ref> He joined Barrow on a five-week loan at the start of the 2009/10 season before returning to Morecambe. He was released by Morecambe in May 2010.<ref>\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/m/morecambe/8703242.stm Morecambe release forward Wayne Curtis]\", ''BBC Sport'' (UK) (25 May 2010).</ref>\n\nHe signed for [[Kendal Town F.C.|Kendal Town]], before switching to [[Witton Albion F.C.|Witton Albion]] on 22 October 2010.<ref>http://www.northwichguardian.co.uk/sport/8472033.Taylor_arrival_boosts_Albion___s_attack/</ref>\n\nHe quickly moved back to Lancashire to join [[Bamber Bridge F.C.|Bamber Bridge]] on 26 November 2010.\nAaron has also played for England youth.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080927102903/http://www.morecambefc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0%2C%2C10866~43789%2C00.html Aaron Taylor profile] at Morecambe F.C.\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Taylor, Aaron (Footballer)}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Morecambe F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Barrow A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Kendal Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Witton Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bamber Bridge F.C. players]]\n\n\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n{{England-footy-forward-1990s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up, remove unref height,typo(s) fixed: 2-2 \u2192 2\u20132", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aaron_Taylor_(footballer)"}
