{"title_page": "Jean-Matthieu Descamps", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jean-Matthieu Descamps\n| image = \n| fullname = Jean-Matthieu Descamps\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1983|2|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Montpellier]], France\n| height = 1.83 m\n| currentclub  = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| youthyears1 = 1995\u20132002\n| youthclubs1 = [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]]\n| years1 = 2002\u20132004\n| clubs1 = [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]]\n| caps1  = 13\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2004\u20132005\n| clubs2 = [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]]<ref name=\"bdfutbol\">{{BDFutbol|4946}}</ref>\n| caps2  = 7\n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2005\u20132006\n| clubs3 = [[FC Libourne-Saint-Seurin|Libourne-Saint-Seurin]]\n| caps3  = 36\n| goals3 = 6\n| years4 = 2006\u20132007\n| clubs4 = [[Racing de Ferrol]]<ref name=\"bdfutbol\"/>\n| caps4  = 15\n| goals4 = 3\n| years5 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs5 = [[FC S\u00e8te|S\u00e8te]]\n| caps5  = 13\n| goals5 = 1\n| years6 = 2008\u20132009\n| clubs6 = [[FC Libourne-Saint-Seurin|Libourne-Saint-Seurin]]\n| caps6  = 29\n| goals6 = 7\n| years7 = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs7 = [[Jura Sud Foot|Jura Sud]]\n| caps7  = 17\n| goals7 = 10\n| years8 = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs8 = [[FC Martigues|Martigues]]\n| caps8  = 64\n| goals8 = 22\n| years9 = 2010\u20132014\n| clubs9 = [[Grenoble Foot 38|Grenoble]]\n| caps9  = 39\n| goals9 = 15\n| totalcaps = 233\n| totalgoals = 64\n}}\n\n'''Jean-Matthieu Descamps''' (born 12 February 1983) is a French former [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]]. He played at the professional level with hometown club [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.laprovence.com/actu/region-en-direct/football-cfa-jean-mathieu-descamps-latout-offensif-martegal | publisher = La Provence | title = Jean-Mathieu Descamps, l'atout offensif mart\u00e9gal |language = French |date = 25 June 2010  | accessdate = 3 January 2010}}</ref> He also had two stints in Spain with [[M\u00e1laga CF|M\u00e1laga]] in the [[2004\u201305 La Liga]] season and with [[Racing de Ferrol]] in the [[Tercera Divisi\u00f3n]] in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.webmhsc.com/anciens-j-m-descamps-signe-a-martigues-av3922.html |publisher=Intensite |title=J-M Descamps signe \u00e0 Martigues |language=French |accessdate=3 January 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100628203352/http://www.webmhsc.com/anciens-j-m-descamps-signe-a-martigues-av3922.html |archivedate=28 June 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{FootballDatabase.eu|961<!-- -jeanmathieu-descamps -->}}\n* {{Lequipe|17030}}\n* {{Webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110415062116/http://lagaseta-football.com/2011/04/12/jean-mathieu-descamps-je-suis-toujours-montpellier/ |title=Interview sur La Gaseta (Avril 2011) }}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Descamps, Jean-Matthieu}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:French footballers]]\n[[Category:French expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:French expatriate sportspeople in Spain]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Spain]]\n[[Category:Montpellier HSC players]]\n[[Category:M\u00e1laga CF players]]\n[[Category:FC S\u00e8te 34 players]]\n[[Category:Racing de Ferrol footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Libourne players]]\n[[Category:Jura Sud Foot players]]\n[[Category:FC Martigues players]]\n[[Category:Grenoble Foot 38 players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Jean-Matthieu Descamps\n| image =\n| fullname = Jean-Matthieu Descamps\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1983|2|12|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Montpellier]], France\n| height = {{height|m=1.83}}\n| currentclub  = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| youthyears1 = 1995\u2013